name: Rhett & Link's Buddy System
overview: Follow best friends, Rhett & Link, as they embark on a fantastical misadventure in search of a missing phone that could save their morning talk show from a co-ex-girlfriend turned evil infomercial queen.

seasons.name: Season 1
seasons.overview: Rhett & Link’s Buddy System follows best friends, Rhett & Link, as they embark on a fantastical misadventure in search of a missing phone that could save their morning talk show from a co-ex-girlfriend turned evil infomercial queen. Starring Rhett and Link (as themselves), Leslie Bibb, Page Kennedy, Chris Parnell, and Molly Shannon.

seasons.name: Season 2 - Another Dimension
seasons.overview: In this particular universe (the one you live in if you're reading this), Rhett and Link are lifelong best friends who met in first grade and host a popular Internet show. But in a parallel universe (which just so happens to be the universe of Rhett & Link's Buddy System: Another Dimension), that meeting never happened. Instead, they meet as adults, and Rhett is a self-absorbed hedonist while Link is alarmingly simple. Will they each be able to grow enough to form the “buddy system” their counterparts enjoy in this universe?

episodes.name: Tucked Up
episodes.overview: Rhett and Link find confidence inside their tucked underwear and use their new-found confidence to face their fears.

episodes.name: Super Special Secret Bike
episodes.overview: To search for the missing phone, Rhett and Link decide to retrace their steps in hopes of finding where they might have lost it, but along the way, Link stumbles upon Rhett's super secret exercise bike.

episodes.name: You Ding, I Ding
episodes.overview: Rhett and Link relive their prom. George doles out parking lot justice.

episodes.name: Rolling On Turds
episodes.overview: Rhett and Link get roped in to rival skating gangs.

episodes.name: The Magic Is Real
episodes.overview: Rhett and Link magically disappear and power rap about a power nap.

episodes.name: Soul Searchin'
episodes.overview: Rhett meets Peder. Link meets Rhett. Things get weird.

episodes.name: Another We
episodes.overview: Rhett and Link confront themselves, and then disguise themselves.

episodes.name: Kill the Naughty Boy
episodes.overview: Will Rhett & Link survive Aimee’s eternal prom?

Starring Rhett and Link (as themselves), Leslie Bibb, Page Kennedy, Chris Parnell, and Molly Shannon.

episodes.name: To Kill a Robot
episodes.overview: In an alternate universe, Rhett and Link never met as kids and thus never became the YouTube stars we know today. Link is fired from his job and evicted from his home, and meets a quirky guy named Rhett who is looking for a roomie.

episodes.name: Sanctuary
episodes.overview: Rhett and Link attempt to find out more about their mysterious roommate Glen, and his connection to a place called The Sanctuary.

episodes.name: Taste Test
episodes.overview: Rhett burns his tongue and loses his extreme tasting abilities, so Link has to step in and take over his job despite his aversion to trying new flavors.

episodes.name: Spa Trip
episodes.overview: A relaxing day at the spa turns into a nightmare when Rhett and Link discover the owner has nefarious purposes.

episodes.name: Virtual Rhettality
episodes.overview: Feeling the urge to become a family man, Link decides to date Vanessa. Meanwhile, Rhett uses a virtual reality game to become his best self -- an overweight middle aged housewife.

episodes.name: A Frontier Story
episodes.overview: A little girl interrupts Rhett and Link's big social plans to tell them the story of 19th Century explorers Rhark and Linkis, who were intent on expanding America's borders inside the earth.

episodes.name: Silent Fight
episodes.overview: A spat about a remote control leads Rhett and Link to give each other the silent treatment, which becomes their ticket to fame and fortune.

episodes.name: A Missing Link
episodes.overview: Rhett and Link go their separate ways to achieve their ultimate destinies, both of which are pretty insane.
